    "They scored higher with lower standard deviations, indicating consistent performance.",
    "Such consistency is vital in medical practice for accurate, reliable disease assessments and trustworthy medical advice.Table 4: Distribution of Top Challenging Questions Across Different Disease Types TOP10Bad A B C D E F G H I J Developmental Delay - - - - - - - - √ - Autism - √ - - - - - - - - (OCD) - - √ - - - - - - - Precocious Puberty √ - - - - - - - - Depression - - - - - - - - - - Tic Disorder √ - - - √ - - - - - Attention De cit Disorder (ADD) - - - - - √ - - - - Anxiety Disorder - - - - - - - - - - Sleep Disorder - - √ - √ - - - - - Anorexia Nervosa √ - - - - - - - - - Discussionour investigation, we conducted an in-depth analysis of ChatGPT-3.5, Claude2, and Google Bard, focusing on how they handle typical inquiries about adolescent growth and development posed by patients and their parents.",
    "Our study employed a solid research methodology, including effective blinding, randomization, and thorough evaluation by expert pediatricians, to ensure the accuracy and reliability of our ndings.",
    "The results indicate that LLM chatbots, especially Claude2, demonstrate pro ciency in delivering precise and detailed answers to questions concerning adolescent growth and development.",
    "Furthermore, our research sheds light on the ability of LLMs to improve their responses' accuracy through self-correction when prompted, a feature not extensively explored in previous studies.It's important to note, though, that these LLMs exhibited limitations in managing more intricate aspects of adolescent growth and development, areas that even human medical professionals nd challenging.Our study is pioneering in its examination of the application of LLMs in this speci c area of medicine, moving beyond the conventional focus of prior research on standardized medical exams."
